          "content": {
            "size": 3309,
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "text": "[{\"type\":\"CONJUNCTION\",\"description\":\"When two planets are in the same sign on your birth chart, it’s called a conjunction. This brings a powerful fusion of energy, amplifying the qualities of both planets. Depending on the planets involved, a conjunction can bring intense passion, focus, or a drive for success in a certain area of life.\"},{\"type\":\"OPPOSITION\",\"description\":\"An opposition occurs when two planets are on the exact opposite sides of your birth chart. This can create tension and a need for balance between the energies of the two planets. You may find yourself torn between two conflicting desires or struggling with inner turmoil, but this aspect can also lead to growth through finding a harmonious balance.\"},{\"type\":\"TRINE\",\"description\":\"When two planets are 120 degrees apart on your birth chart, it's called a trine. This aspect creates a harmonious flow of energy between the planets, allowing them to work together in a positive way. It often brings good luck, smooth relationships, and easy expressions of natural talents.\"},{\"type\":\"SQUARE\",\"description\":\"The square aspect occurs when two planets are 90 degrees apart on your birth chart. This creates a challenging dynamic, often causing tension and difficulties in life. However, it also creates a sense of motivation and drive, pushing you to overcome obstacles, learn, and grow.\"},{\"type\":\"SEXTILE\",\"description\":\"A sextile aspect is formed when two planets are 60 degrees apart on your birth chart. This aspect brings a harmonious energy between the planets, allowing their energies to work together in a beneficial way. It often brings opportunities for growth and creative expression.\"},{\"type\":\"QUINCUNX\",\"description\":\"The Quincunx aspect, also known as a quincunx, happens when two planets are 150 degrees apart on your birth chart. This aspect can bring feelings of restlessness and uncertainty as the energies of the planets clash. However, it also urges you to embrace change and adapt to new situations.\"},{\"type\":\"QUINTILE\",\"description\":\"When two planets are 72 degrees apart on your birth chart, it creates a quintile aspect. This aspect can indicate inspiration and creativity, as well as opportunities to express your unique talents in a beneficial way. It can also bring a sense of purpose in certain areas of your life.\"},{\"type\":\"SEMI-SEXTILE\",\"description\":\"The semi-sextile aspect occurs when two planets are 30 degrees apart on your birth chart. This aspect indicates a harmonious flow of energy, allowing the planets to work together smoothly. It may bring small but significant opportunities for growth and development in your life.\"},{\"type\":\"SEMI-SQUARE\",\"description\":\"When two planets are 45 degrees apart on your birth chart, it forms a semi-square aspect. This can bring tension and inner conflict, but also drive to overcome challenges. It can motivate you to make necessary changes and highlight areas of your life that need attention.\"},{\"type\":\"SESQUIQUADRATE\",\"description\":\"The sesquiquadrate aspect, also known as a trioctile, occurs when two planets are 135 degrees apart on your birth chart. This aspect can bring a sense of discomfort as the planets have conflicting energies. However, it also offers an opportunity to find creative solutions and make adjustments to reach harmony.\"}]"
          },
          "redirectURL": "",
          "bodySize": -1
        },
        "startedDateTime": "2026-02-28T04:48:42.036Z"
      },
